cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this code or the HalluProbe-VL probe set, please cite the paper below."
title: "Hierarchical Grounding Fusion for Detecting and Mitigating Object, Attribute, and Relation Hallucinations in Multimodal Large Language Models"
abstract: >-
  A training-free, plug-and-play framework that fuses off-the-shelf grounding
  evidence to detect object, attribute, and relation hallucinations in multimodal
  large language models, to mitigate object hallucination by detect-then-revise,
  and to improve yes/no answering by calibrated decision fusion. Demonstrated on
  four backbones (LLaVA-1.5, LLaVA-1.6, InstructBLIP, Qwen-VL) with no fine-tuning.
  Also releases HalluProbe-VL, a leak-free diagnostic for three-kind detection.
